  "time_ut": 1658818285,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0dd9\u0da7\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dbd\u0dca \u0d89\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dd6 \u0daf\u0dd9\u0daf\u0dbb\u0dd4 \u0db4\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0da7 \u0db4\u0ddc\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The father of two who asked for petrol was attacked by the police",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A hospital spokesperson said that a father of two children was admitted to the Panadura Basic Hospital yesterday afternoon (25th) after he was brutally assaulted by the police after a conversation with the police asking for petrol.",
        "Samantha Rajapaksa, a 49-year-old father of two, a resident of Wavulugala, Maggona, was assaulted and taken to hospital.",
        "Bruises, scratches and swelling injuries could be seen in about 15 places including his ankle, buttocks, feet, shoulder, sandalwood, lip and near the ear.",
        "His 14-year-old son, who is being treated in Panadura Base Hospital, was seen holding the parcel of rice brought to his father and crying with tears in his eyes.",
        "I am a taxi driver. Maggona was in the queue at Sipetco filling station since 20th, there was no petrol in the filling station. But on the night of the 24th, a police jeep was parked to cover the pump and got petrol for cans and other motorcycles. I also asked for 2 liters of oil. Later, the police beat me and put me in the jeep and took me to the Payagala police station and brutally beat me.",
        "Later that night, two police officers took me out of the cell, handcuffed me to the teeth, and kicked me with a stick and hand. I have about 20 wounds on my body.",
        "Yesterday evening (25th), I was granted bail after being presented before the Kalutara Magistrate under the charge of being an unlawful mass in the cell.",
        "In this regard, he has also complained to the Panadura Human Rights Office. Panadura Hospital Police took statements."
      ],
